17. The Investment Policy shall, at the minimum, include:
(1). The investment criteria and objectives to be achieved while undertaking
investment transactions on bank's own investment account and on behalf
of clients;
(2). Securities in which investments can be made by the bank;
(3). Derivatives in which the bank shall deal;
(4). The authority to put through deals;
(5). Procedure for obtaining the sanction of the appropriate authority and putting
through deals;
(6). Adherence to various prudential exposure limits; and
(7). Policy regarding dealings through brokers, systems for management of
various risks, guidelines for valuation of the portfolio, and the reporting
systems.
